race.comment: WHO SAZ YES (6) comes here off a 54-day break where she disappointed at Belmont, jumping a $7.50 chance. Back in grade today, she looks well placed despite the sticky barrier. Back to this trip on the fresh side looks ideal and she can put her best foot forward. RIVERCREST MAGIC (10) finished 1.8L off the winner last start at Belmont and the rating from that event stacks up in this race. She'll need some luck from the barrier, though she tends to get back in her races anyway. Can storm over the top with the winkers replacing the blinkers. THE CHIEF JUSTICE (8) bolted in at the trials coming into this and has won 2/4 first-up in the past. The blinkers come off now, but he should land on the speed and is expected to be hard to run down. DISCO KICKS (3) just missed last time out at Toodyay and should get her chance to go one better from the barrier. CHEST OUT SWAGGER (5) can feature in the finish once again.
